data.description: House-hackers, investors and primary homeowners rejoice! The home is the perfect balance between suburban tranquility and urban convenience. You’ll drive through the quaint a peaceful Edinburg Village, which is located in downtown West Windsor, and you’ll come upon the property. Pulling down the oversized driveway towards the detached two-car garage, you’ll notice the size and charm of the property. Both units are currently rented, with the lease on the right side unit ending in May 2024 and the other in October 2024. One side is a two bed, one and a half bath and the other side is a two bed, one bath that have both been tastefully updated. The charm of the property has been carefully maintained, but has been updated with modern finishes. The home has a newer roof (9 years old), public sewer, public water, and natural gas. The unit on the left side is currently rented for $2,300 so, if you’re looking to house-hack, you can significantly reduce your monthly payment while building equity and benefitting from West Windsors rapidly appreciating market (an 11.6% increase in 2023). Just a stones throw away from Dutch Neck Elementary school, with easy walking paths there, and with access to West Windsor-Plainsboro’s Blue Ribbon schools, as well as easy access to the West Windsor train station (West Windsor residents get priority access to parking at the train station), this home has everything and more. There are only a handful of multi-family units in West Windsor, so don’t miss out!
